9 ounce Cheese Tortelloni
14 ounce Marinara Cup

Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add tortelloni and reduce heat to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tortelloni are al dente and floating to the top, 3-5 minutes. Drain.

Heat a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add marinara and bring to a low simmer. Gently stir in drained tortelloni until coated.

Divide between bowls and serve.

Recipe suggestion (additional ingredients not included): Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium high heat. Add 2 cloves thinly sliced garlic and a pinch of chili flakes; cook until fragrant, 30 seconds. Pour in marinara and bring to a simmer, then gently stir in drained tortelloni until coated. Divide between bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan. Top with chopped fresh basil or parsley.